        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17223",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assigned to Rob",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-15T13:47:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-15T13:47:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17272",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I like the idea of post-construction configurability, but I would instead recommend the solution to be adding a {{setAllowModifications(boolean $enabled)}} method or similar, though maybe there is better name for {{$enabled}}.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-17T07:49:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-17T07:49:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17296",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "setAllowModifications() implies that a Zend_Config object can be made writable at will. \n\nMaybe something like setReadOnly() so that it's a one-way operation ?\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-18T02:15:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-18T02:15:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17326",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I also think disallowing modifications should be one-way as it's something you'd do to enforce code standards. The name (seal() or setReadOnly()) doesn't matter to me.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-19T15:35:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-19T15:35:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17327",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If I understand correctly, this is trivially accomplished by extending Zend_Config:\n\n{code}\nclass MyConfig extends Zend_Config\n{\n    public function seal()\n    {\n        $this->_allowModifications = false;\n        return $this;\n    }\n}\n{code}\n\nConsidering the above comments and the fact that it could also be harmful to allow only {{seal()}}\/{{setReadOnly()}} - many people would have the opposite problem (needing write access to a locked object) - it would seem that this is best done in userland instead of bloating the framework component with possibly problematic functionality.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-19T15:45:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-19T15:45:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17329",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It's not that easy because you need to apply the change recursively. And that's currently not possible because __construct() and __set() use new Zend_Config instead of new self and therefor all childs won't have a seal method.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-19T17:02:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-19T17:02:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17442",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, of course, I missed that. What would the implementation look like, now that I committed [SVN r6767|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/fisheye\/changelog\/Zend_Framework\/?cs=6767]?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-07T13:01:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-07T13:01:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17555",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Nico,\n\nDoes Darby's change in SVN r6767 allow you to solve your problem if you write the userland class :\n\n{code}class MyConfig extends Zend_Config\n{\n    public function seal()\n    {\n        $this->_allowModifications = false;\n        return $this;\n    }\n}{code}\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-15T10:28:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-15T10:28:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17691",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'd like to resolve this issue one way or another if possible.\n\nChoices are:\n\n1. Resolve as \"Won't Fix\" or \"Not an Issue\" and users will have to create a user-land class.\n2. Add a setReadOnly() function to Zend_Config.\n\n\nPersonally, I'm tending towards (2) as merging multiple config files into a single Zend_Config doesn't strike me as that unusual a use-case and with merge() we are implicitly endorsing this use-case anyway. May as well tidy up after ourselves!\n\nThoughts?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-23T17:48:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-23T17:48:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17738",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Added setReadOnly() in [svn 6967|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/fisheye\/changelog\/Zend_Framework\/?cs=6967] on the trunk and [svn 6968|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/fisheye\/changelog\/Zend_Framework\/?cs=6968] on the release-1.0 branch.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-27T14:51:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-27T14:51:13.000+0000"
                },
